# Observability Standards — Bunyan

## Structured Logging

Always use structured context arrays — never plain string messages.

### Backend (Laravel)

```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Log;

// Correct — structured context
Log::info('Project created', [
    'project_id' => $project->id,
    'user_id'    => $user->id,
    'action'     => 'project.created',
]);

Log::error('Payment failed', [
    'order_id' => $order->id,
    'user_id'  => $user->id,
    'error'    => $exception->getMessage(),
    'action'   => 'payment.failed',
]);

// Wrong — no context
Log::info('Project was created');
```

### Required Context Fields

| Situation                      | Required Fields                                                    |
| ------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Entity created/updated/deleted | `action`, `<entity>_id`, `user_id`                                 |
| API request/response           | `method`, `url`, `status`, `user_id`, `ip`, `duration_ms`          |
| Workflow state transition      | `action`, `entity_id`, `from_status`, `to_status`, `user_id`       |
| Authentication event           | `action`, `user_id`, `ip`                                          |
| Payment/financial              | `action`, `order_id`, `user_id`, `amount` — log to `audit` channel |
| Queue job failure              | `action`, `job_class`, `attempt`, `error`                          |
| Error/exception                | `action`, `error`, all relevant IDs                                |

## Log Channels

```php
// config/logging.php
'channels' => [
    'daily' => [
        'driver' => 'daily',
        'path'   => storage_path('logs/laravel.log'),
        'days'   => 14,
    ],
    'audit' => [
        'driver' => 'daily',
        'path'   => storage_path('logs/audit.log'),
        'days'   => 90,
    ],
],
```

- **`daily`**: General application events (info, warnings, errors)
- **`audit`**: Financial and sensitive operations (payments, role changes, withdrawals)

## Request Logging Middleware

```php
class RequestLogger
{
    public function handle(Request $request, Closure $next): Response
    {
        $response = $next($request);

        Log::channel('requests')->info('API Request', [
            'method'      => $request->method(),
            'url'         => $request->fullUrl(),
            'status'      => $response->status(),
            'user_id'     => $request->user()?->id,
            'ip'          => $request->ip(),
            'duration_ms' => round((microtime(true) - LARAVEL_START) * 1000),
        ]);

        return $response;
    }
}
```

## Workflow State Transitions

Log every status change through the workflow engine:

```php
Log::info('Workflow transition', [
    'action'      => 'workflow.transition',
    'entity_type' => 'project',
    'entity_id'   => $project->id,
    'from_status' => $oldStatus,
    'to_status'   => $newStatus,
    'user_id'     => $user->id,
]);
```

## Hard Rules

- **NEVER** log passwords, tokens, secrets, or payment card details
- **ALWAYS** use `Log::audit()` (or `Log::channel('audit')`) for financial operations
- **ALWAYS** log authentication failures (failed logins, unauthorized access)
- **NEVER** swallow exceptions silently — log with full context before re-throwing
- Log levels: `debug` (dev only), `info` (state changes), `warning` (recoverable), `error` (failures), `critical` (data integrity)

## Monitoring Checklist

- [ ] All API endpoints log request/response status
- [ ] Authentication events logged (login, logout, failed attempts)
- [ ] Workflow state transitions logged with before/after status
- [ ] Payment/financial operations logged to `audit` channel
- [ ] Queue job failures logged with full context and attempt count
- [ ] Error responses include enough context for root cause analysis
